d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal : Rule Change - 40 planeables</span><hr size=1> As another member of Guardians of Twilight, but not posting as a representative as such, I also agree with Daia in that changing the number isn't going to make much difference in the weekday bookings, and will definitely make the weekend bookings much more difficult for guilds and alliances like ours which do have at least 40 planesable members (I believe that GoT is up around at least 80 at this point).  <br>
We get Fear and Hate about once a month each...on weekends which is when we can muster 25-30 folks to go...if the number for reserving planes was lowered to 30, we might not even get THAT many shots, and plenty of folks in our 2 respective guilds still need various pieces of planar armor due to rarity of drops, not having been there on the last raid, etc.  I feel that this would apply to any other guild/alliance of our size as well.  <br>
Ten people doesn't seem like a lot, but consider that we'd probably be allowing at least 10 more guilds to schedule raids...with roughly 8 weekend days a month...we could be looking at a 2-3 month waiting time to get Fear on a Saturday!!<br>
