<br>
I personally agree with both Daia and Delissandra.<br>
<br>
The night we finished our last Hate raid, I immediately went to the calendar to see when the next weekend date was open.  It was 1 month from that day approx. so I penciled it in.  Now, I want to mention that our last two hate raids have had to be on a Sunday because If I want a Saturday raid I need to schedule almost 2 months out already.  Lowering the standard to 30 will do nothing but make &quot;scheduling&quot; a day useless, guilds do not want to have to wait 3 months to go to the planes.<br>
<br>
Something everyone should be aware of is that this cycle happens every year, as soon as school starts the calendar is full almost every weekend out, due to most people that go to school can't spend a full 8 - 14 hours online one day during the week for a plane raid, they have to do it on the weekend.  Next summer this won't be much of an issue because the guilds will be filling up the weekday slots again.<br>
<br>
Another thing to realize is that the days that there is nobody posted, you can go to that plane.  If I remember correctly a long time ago there was a post stating that unreserved days are considered FFA on that day, as long as you were out by the normal RTA cut off time. <p><a href="http://www.ringofdragons.com"><img src="http://www.ionet.net/~sidhe/rodsig/doraedin.jpg"></a><br><br><font face="Tahoma" size=4>Death is lighter than a feather, Duty heavier than a mountain.</font>
